cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to estimate the importance of objects in on-road driving videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel framework for object importance estimation, which involves updating the features of each object node by interacting with others through graph convolution. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with autonomous driving systems, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for pre-processing, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
